HEADWORD: Lilly-pilly
<hw>Lil"ly-pil`ly</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧l"l⟦ycr⟧-p⟦icr⟧l`l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An Australian myrtaceous tree
(<spn>Eugenia Smithii</spn>), having smooth ovate leaves, and panicles
of small white flowers. The wood is hard and fine-grained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

